#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:1
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:3
msgid "What is the origin of the name Nix?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:5
msgid ""
"The name *Nix* is derived from the Dutch word *niks*, meaning *nothing*; "
"build actions do not see anything that has not been explicitly declared as "
"an input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:8
msgid ""
"&mdash; <cite>[Nix: A Safe and Policy-Free System for Software Deployment]"
"(https://edolstra.github.io/pubs/nspfssd-lisa2004-final.pdf), LISA XVIII, "
"2004</cite>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:8
msgid "<cite>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:8
msgid "</cite>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:10
msgid ""
"The Nix logo is inspired by [an idea for the Haskell logo](https://wiki."
"haskell.org/File:Sgf-logo-blue.png) and the fact that [*nix* is Latin for "
"*snow*](https://nix-dev.science.uu.narkive.com/VDaaP1BY/nix-logo)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:12
msgid "What are flakes?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:14
msgid "See [](flakes-definition)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:17
msgid "Which channel branch should I use?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:19
msgid "Nixpkgs and NixOS have both stable and rolling releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:21
msgid ""
"These releases are distributed in variants called \"channel branches\": Git "
"branches used for releases, which are also converted to Nix channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:25
msgid ""
"Consult the [`nix-channel`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/2.22/command-ref/nix-"
"channel) entry in the Nix Reference Manual for more information on channels, "
"and the [Nixpkgs contributing guide](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/"
"master/CONTRIBUTING.md#branch-conventions) on the Nixpkgs branching strategy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:28
msgid "Stable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:30
msgid ""
"Stable releases receive conservative updates to fix bugs or security "
"vulnerabilities; otherwise package versions are not changed. A new stable "
"release is made every six months."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:33
msgid ""
"On Linux (including NixOS and WSL), use [`nixos-*`](https://github.com/NixOS/"
"nixpkgs/branches/all?query=nixos-)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:35
msgid ""
"These branches point to commits where most Linux packages got pre-built and "
"can be fetched from the binary cache. Furthermore, these commits passed the "
"full NixOS test suite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:38
msgid ""
"On macOS/Darwin, use [`nixpkgs-*-darwin`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"branches/all?query=nixpkgs-)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:40
msgid ""
"These branches point to commits where most Darwin packages got pre-built and "
"can be fetched from the binary cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:42
msgid "On any other platform it doesn't matter which one of the above is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:44
msgid "Hydra doesn't pre-build any binaries for other platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:46
msgid ""
"All of these \"channel branches\" follow the corresponding [`release-*`]"
"(https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/branches/all?query=release-) branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:48
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:49
msgid ""
"`nixos-23.05` and `nixpkgs-23.05-darwin` are both based on `release-23.05`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:52
msgid "Rolling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:54
msgid ""
"Rolling releases follow [`master`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/branches/"
"all?query=master), the main development branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:56
msgid ""
"On Linux (including NixOS and WSL), use [`nixos-unstable`](https://github."
"com/NixOS/nixpkgs/branches/all?query=nixos-unstable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:57
msgid ""
"On any other platform, use [`nixpkgs-unstable`](https://github.com/NixOS/"
"nixpkgs/branches/all?query=nixpkgs-unstable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:59
msgid ""
"[`*-small`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/branches/all?query=-small) "
"channel branches have passed a smaller test suite, which means they are more "
"up-to-date with respect to their base branch, but offer fewer stability "
"guarantees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:61
msgid "Are there any impurities left in sandboxed builds?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:63
msgid "Yes. There is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:65
msgid ""
"CPU architecture—great effort is being made to avoid compilation of native "
"instructions in favour of hardcoded supported ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:66
msgid "System's current time/date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:67
msgid ""
"The filesystem used for building (see also [`TMPDIR`](https://nix.dev/manual/"
"nix/stable/command-ref/env-common.html#env-TMPDIR))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:68
msgid "Linux kernel parameters, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:69
msgid "[IPv6 capabilities](https://github.com/NixOS/nix/issues/5615)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:70
msgid ""
"binfmt interpreters, e.g., those configured with [`boot.binfmt."
"emulatedSystems`](https://search.nixos.org/options?show=boot.binfmt."
"emulatedSystems)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:71
msgid ""
"Timing behaviour of the build system—a parallel Make build may not get the "
"correct inputs in some cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:72
msgid "Insertion of random values, e.g., from `/dev/random` or `/dev/urandom`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../concepts/faq.md:73
msgid ""
"Differences between Nix versions. For instance, a new Nix version might "
"introduce a new environment variable. A statement like `env > $out` is not "
"promised by Nix to result in the same output, going into the future."
msgstr ""
